Mnh, the script warns that there are some "Possible missing libraries", and they look
important, so let's make the script add them:


	$ pacman2appDir flightgear -subversion --auto-copy-libs


	...
	Possible missing libraries: (use --auto-copy-libs to copy them into usr/lib/)
	‘/usr/lib/libglapi.so.0’ -> ‘usr/lib/libglapi.so.0’
	‘/usr/lib/libGL.so.1’ -> ‘usr/lib/libGL.so.1’
	‘/usr/lib/libglut.so.3’ -> ‘usr/lib/libglut.so.3’
	‘/usr/lib/libopenal.so.1’ -> ‘usr/lib/libopenal.so.1’
	‘/usr/lib/libpng15.so.15’ -> ‘usr/lib/libpng15.so.15’
	‘/usr/lib/libsystemd-daemon.so.0’ -> ‘usr/lib/libsystemd-daemon.so.0’
	‘/usr/lib/libudev.so.1’ -> ‘usr/lib/libudev.so.1’
	...


Done, now let's package it


	$ buildAppImage


There, done!
